      aiAnswer: { question: `How much do I need for retirement in ${loc}?`, answer: `A comfortable retirement for a single Australian requires approximately $51,278/year according to the ASFA Retirement Standard, with the Age Pension providing $29,754 as a base. To generate $21,524 from savings using the 4% rule, you need approximately $538,000 in super. Our retirement calculator factors in the Super Guarantee (11.5% rising to 12%), investment returns, and Age Pension eligibility to project your retirement readiness.` },
